SUMMARY:Emmet Cohen presents: Miles and Coltrane at 100
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the centennial of John Coltrane and Miles Davis\, pianist Emmet Cohen brings together an all-star quintet to explore the fundamental questions that shaped their artistry: Why are we here? What are we reaching for? Where does the music take us? \nA dynamic ensemble led by pianist Emmet Cohen\, featuring saxophonist Tivon Pennicott and trumpeter Jeremy Pelt will celebrate these geniuses in Miles and Coltrane at 100. \nGuided by the spirit of the infinite\, Cohen continues the journey set forth by the architects of jazz — seeking deeper truths through sound. \nA dedicated champion of the musical community\, Cohen believes in jazz as a living\, evolving conversation — one that unites people across time and place. \nJoin Cohen and his ensemble for a bold\, reimagined experience of the music that forever changed the course of jazz. \nSupported in part by Oliver’s Markets and Balletto Vineyards
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/emmet-cohen-presents-miles-and-coltrane-at-100/
LOCATION:Green Music Center\, Weill Hall\, Sonoma State University\, 1801 East Cotati Avenue\, Rohnert Park\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
