SUMMARY:The Christians presented by the Cinnabar Theater
DESCRIPTION:Cinnabar Theater presents The Christians by Lucas Hnath \nA powerful\, thought-provoking drama about faith\, conviction\, and the cost of standing by your beliefs. \nWhen a beloved megachurch pastor delivers a sermon that challenges a core doctrine\, his congregation is thrown into turmoil. What follows is an intimate and gripping exploration of belief\, doubt\, leadership\, and community—inviting audiences to wrestle with big questions that linger long after the final moment on stage. \n• Warren Theater\, Sonoma State University (Ives Hall)\, 1801 East Cotati Ave\, Rohnert Park\, CA 94928\n• April 10–26\, 2026\n• Fridays & Saturdays at 7:30 PM | Sundays at 2:00 PM\n• Special Talkback Post Show: Sunday\, April 19 \nDirected by Nathan Cummings and featuring a stellar cast\, this minimalist\, emotionally resonant production is recommended for mature audiences.\nTickets: cinnabartheater.org
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/the-christians-presented-by-the-cinnabar-theater/
LOCATION:Sonoma State University – Warren Theater\, Located in Ives Hall\, 1801 East Cotati Ave\, Rohnert Park\, CA
CATEGORIES:Theater
